      "content" : "<p>\n\tAccording to a meta-analysis performed by Clarke MA et al. 9% of women with postmenopausal bleeding have endometrial cancer. The authors analyzed data from 40790 unique patients in 129 studies&nbsp;published January 1, 1977, through January 31, 2017.&nbsp;They found that 90% of women&nbsp;with endometrial cancerhave&nbsp;postmenopausal bleeding; however, only 9% of women with postmenopausal bleeding were diagnosed with endometrial cancer.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n\tSource:<br />\n\t<a href=\"https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamainternalmedicine/article-abstract/2695509\">https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamainternalmedicine/article-abstract/2695509</a></p>",
