      "excerpt" : "Professor Dr. Cem Uzun, Editor-at-Large of Balkan Medical Journal, was elected as a Member of the European Association of Science Editors (EASE) Council at the meeting held on 10 March 2018. For the first time in the...",
      "title" : "Professor Dr. Cem Uzun, Editor at-Large of Balkan Medical Journal, is at the EASE Council.",
      "image" : "images/placeholder-news.jpg",
      "content" : "<p>\n\tProfessor Dr. Cem Uzun, Editor-at-Large of Balkan Medical Journal, was elected as a Member of the European Association of Science Editors (EASE)&nbsp;&nbsp;Council at the meeting held on 10 March 2018. For the first time in the history of EASE, founded in 1982, Turkish Scientist was selected for the EASE Council.</p>\n<p>\n\tIn his statement on the issue &quot;Our efforts in terms of scientific publications in Turkey and the Balkan countries was an important factor in this appointment. We aim to promote, raise awareness, coordinate and contribute to the development of scientific publishing in the Balkan countries,&quot; Professor Uzun said.</p>\n<p>\n\tProfessor Uzun will perform this task between 2018 and 2021.</p>",
